en drain the solution from the 20l kettle into the 15l kettle','',0,12,2,'','[]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]'),(188,'test@example.com','15AG10i11','Leave the sterilisng solution for a few minutes in the 15l kettle, then ensure all surfaces are covered before draining into the fermentation bin','',0,12,3,'','[]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]'),(189,'test@example.com','15AG10i11','Leave the sterilisng solution for a few minutes in the fermentation bin, then ensure all surfaces are covered before discarding','',0,12,4,'','[]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]'),(190,'test@example.com','15AG10i11','Rinse Equipment','',0,13,-1,'Rinse Equipment in the same way as sterilising, equipment should be rinsed wiht 25 litres of cold water.','[]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]'),(191,'test@example.com','15AG10i11','Assemble Sparge Setup and begin Recirculation','',0,14,-1,'Once the sparge water is at the correct temperature ...sparge_temp...C AND the mash duration has completedthe sparge setup can be setup. During this step the cloudy wort with bits of grain will drained leading to a natural grain filter forming.','[\"spargesetup.png\"]','Set the thermometer to alarm if the temperature is higher than 71deg. If it is then lid should be lifted to reduce the heat.','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]'),(192,'test@example.com','15AG10i11','Take off the lid from the mash tun and assemble the sparge arm','',0,14,0,'','[]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'',0,0,'[]'),(193,'test@example.com','15AG10i11','Allow up to 6 litres of wort to drain from the mash tun into the kettle, the wort should be carefully added back to the top of the lauter tun trying to ensure minimal disturbance.','',0,14,1,'','[]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]'),(194,'test@example.com','15AG10i11','Start Fly Sparging','',0,15,-1,'Sparging will drain the sugar from the grain providing us with wort. The process of sparging should be carried out slowly. The aim is to keep an inch of water above the top of the grain bed throughout the process. The temperature of the ga