.com','16AG11i12','If not using bottled water for the Mash Liquid crush half a Campden tablet into the water and leave for 5 minutes. Leave a further 5 minutes and there stir well.','',0,7,1,'','[]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]'),(311,'test@example.com','16AG11i12','Begin heating the mash liquid to ...strike_temp_5...C, continue with other steps in the background.','',0,7,2,'','[]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]'),(312,'test@example.com','16AG11i12','Rinse Mash Tun and equipment','',0,8,-1,'Rinse Equipment in the same way as sterilsing, equipment should be rinsed with 25 litres of cold water. ','[]','The storage box and equipment is not sterilised, some equipment will need to remain sterilised throughout.','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]'),(313,'test@example.com','16AG11i12','Ensure all surfaces of the storage box are sterilised and then drain the sterilising solution from the storage box.','',0,8,0,'','[]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]'),(314,'test@example.com','16AG11i12','Ensure all surfaces of the mash tun (inside and out) and rinsed and then drain water into the storage box.','',0,8,1,'','[]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]'),(315,'test@example.com','16AG11i12','Ensure lids for the hot liquor tun and mash tun are rinsed from sterilising solution.','',0,8,2,'','[]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]'),(316,'test@example.com','16AG11i12','Discard the water from the storage box and add 10 litres of cold water to the mash tun and repeat the rinsing, then drain water into the storage box.','',0,8,3,'','[]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]'),(317,'test@example.com','16AG11i12','Add 7L of water from the now sterilised storage box into the 20l kettle ready for the next sterilising.','',0,8,4,'','[]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]'),(318,'test@example.com','16AG11i12','Get Ready to Mash','',0,9,-1,'During the mash the complex starches into simple sugars suitable for fermentation. The mash-tun is pre-heated during this step to minimise the heat lost to the cold mashtun. During mashing temperature control is important but an insulated mash tun will not change significantly over an hour.  ','[]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'grainqty',1,0,'[]'),(319,'test@example.com','16AG11i12','Boil 1.5L of tap water and add to the mash tun, add the lid to the mash tun','',0,9,0,'','[]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]'),(320,'test@example.com','16AG11i12','Add 2 teaspoons of burton water salts to the grain.','',0,9,1,'','[]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]'),(321,'test@example.com','16AG11i12','Fill the mash tun with mash liquid','',0,10,-1,'Fill the mashtun with the mash liquor in order the water is to ...strike_temp...C (Strike Temp ...strike_temp...C). The water in the HLT should be heated to 5degC higher than strke temp to account for some losses while transferring the liquid, however the temperature should be monitored.','[\"mash_setup.png\"]','If the grain temperature is not between 15-20 degC then the calculations should be re-run to provide a hotter/colder strike temp.','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]'),(322,'test@example.com','16AG11i12','Discard the water used for preheating the mash tun into the 20l kettle','',0,10,0,'','[]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]'),(323,'test@example.com','16AG11i12','Fill the mash tun with  ...mash_liquid...L of water heated to ...strike_temp_5...C.','',0,10,1,'','[]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]'),(324,'test@example.com','16AG11i12','Set aside 1.7L of boiling water and 1.7L of cold water which may optionally may be used for adjustment of temperature/consistency','',0,10,2,'','[]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]'),(325,'test@example.com','16AG11i12','Dough in the grain','',0,11,-1,'The temperature for mashing is important high temperatures will lead to extraction of tannins, low temperatures will not provide efficient conversion. Lower temperature conversion - around 64-66.6C  will take longer but will produce a more complete conversion of complex starches to sugars resulting in more fermentation and a clean, lighter tasting beer. A high temperature conversion of 68.5-70 C will result in le