s of cold water.','[]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]'),(909,'test@example.com','9AG3i4','Get Ready to Mash','',0,6,-1,'During the mash the complex starches into simple sugars suitable for fermentation. During mashing temperature control is important but an insulated mash tun will not change significantly over an hour.','[]','Do not turn on the temperature controller until the elements in the kettle are covered with water.','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]'),(910,'test@example.com','9AG3i4','Fill the hot liquor tank with ...sparge_water...L of water for the sparging','',0,6,0,'','[]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]'),(911,'test@example.com','9AG3i4','Fill the mash tun with mash liquid. During this step the mash tun should be well insulated.','',0,7,-1,'','[\"mash_setup.png\"]','If the grain temperature is not within 15-20 degC then the calculations should be re-run to provide a hotter/colder strike temp.','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]'),(912,'test@example.com','9AG3i4','Fill the mash tun with  ...mash_liquid...L of water heated to ...strike_temp_5...C. The water will take approximately ...sparge_heating_time... minutes to heat','',0,7,0,'','[]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]'),(913,'test@example.com','9AG3i4','Set aside the grain ready to stir into the mash tun when the temperature reduces to ...strike_temp...','',0,7,1,'','[]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]'),(914,'test@example.com','9AG3i4','Set aside 1.7L of boiling water and 1.7L of cold water which may optionally may be used for adjustment of temperature.','',0,7,2,'','[]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]'),(915,'test@example.com','9AG3i4','Dough in the grain','',0,8,-1,'The temperature for mashing is important high temperatures will lead to extraction of tannins, low temperatures will not provide efficient conversion. Try: An optional sterilised spoon tied to a mixer with plastic ties may be used to save mixing','[]','The Temperature of the Grain Bed should remain below 75degC throughout','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]'),(916,'test@example.com','9AG3i4','With the temperature of the mash liquid at ...strike_temp...C stir in the grain.','',0,8,0,'','[]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]'),(917,'test@example.com','9AG3i4','The aim is to mash at a temperature of ...target_mash_temp...C. If the temperature difference is +/- 3degC then an adjustment may be carried out.','',0,8,1,'','[]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]'),(918,'test@example.com','9AG3i4','If satisifed with the temperature then cover and set aside for 60 minutes.','',0,8,2,'','[]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]'),(919,'test@example.com','9AG3i4','Fill the HLT and begin heating','',0,9,-1,'Fill the HLT with ...sparge_water... L of sparge water. The sparge water is expected to take around ...sparge_heating_time... minutes to heat.','[]','The HLT is constructed with standard kettle elements, therefore it is advisable to alternate between the elements 3 or 4 times during the heating. The temperature controller should only power one kettle element at any time.','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]'),(920,'test@example.com','9AG3i4','Sterilise Part 2','',0,10,-1,'It is important throughout the brew day to ensure that equipment which comes into contact with the wort is sterilised. This step focuses on the equipment needed after the mashing.','[]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]'),(921,'test@example.com','9AG3i4','Fill the large kettle with 15 litres of warm water and 3 tsp of sterilising powder.','',0,10,0,'','[]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]'),(922,'test@example.com','9AG3i4','Add the thermometers, hydrometer and trial jar, slotted spoon, optional immersion heater, and small jug to the kettle. Ensure that all sides of the large kettle are rinsed','',0,10,1,'','[]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]'),(923,'test@example.com','9AG3i4','Ensure all surfaces and equipment are well covered with sterilising solution (including lids). Then drain the solution from the 20l kettle into the 15l kettle','',0,10,2,'','[]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]'),(924,'test@example.com','9AG3i4','Leave the sterilisng solution for a 