 start allowing water from the hot liquor tun (HLT) slowly','',0,13,0,'','[]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]'),(932,'test@example.com','9AG3i4','After the sparge volume is reached or the gravity of the runoff is below 1.006 then stop sparging. Transfer some of the early runoff\'s from the 20l kettle into the 15l kettle so that the volumes are roughly equal','',0,13,1,'','[]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]'),(933,'test@example.com','9AG3i4','Dynamic Recipe Adjustment','',0,14,-1,'If the mash was particularly efficent/inefficient it may be desirarble to top up fermentables, dilute wort, increase/decrease hop quantities.','[]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'dynamicrecipeadjustment',1,0,'[]'),(934,'test@example.com','9AG3i4','Bring the Wort to the boil','',0,15,-1,'Boiling the wort extracts bitterness and aroma from the hops, driving off unwanted volatile components, coagulates proteins,  and sanitising the wort for fermentation','[]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]'),(935,'test@example.com','9AG3i4','Measure Hops','',0,16,-1,'Measure the hops and place aside ready to add during the boil.','[]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'hopmeasure',1,0,'[]'),(936,'test@example.com','9AG3i4','Hop Additions','',0,17,-1,'Boiling the wort extracts bitterness and aroma from the hops','[]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'hopaddition',1,0,'[]'),(937,'test@example.com','9AG3i4','Once the wort has reached a good rolling boil leave the lids half covering the stock pot.','',0,17,0,'','[]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]'),(938,'test@example.com','9AG3i4','Boil Yeast Rehydration Water','',0,18,-1,'Rehydration yeast prvoides a gentle start for the yeast and helps fermentation start quickly.','[]','Yeast should nto be added to the rehydration water unless is is &lt;25 degC','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]'),(939,'test@example.com','9AG3i4','Boil 500ml of water and set aside in a pyrex jug','',0,18,0,'','[]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]'),(940,'test@example.com','9AG3i4','After 10 minutes put the hug in a water bath to cool the water to 25 degC','',0,18,1,'','[]',''